  "prompt": "What art print could complement the Brooklyn bridge art print by Andy Warhol?",
  "response": "To complement the Brooklyn Bridge art print by Andy Warhol, you might consider other pieces that blend urban themes, pop art style, and iconic structures. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Statue of Liberty by Andy Warhol:** This print offers similar themes, and Warhol\u2019s unique style would create a visually cohesive and iconic display.\n\n2. **Empire State Building by Andy Warhol:** Another New York City landmark captured in Warhol's distinct style would enhance the metropolitan vibe.\n\n3. **Times Square by Roy Lichtenstein:** Lichtenstein\u2019s pop art and comic book aesthetic focusing on New York's vibrant scene would pair well with Warhol's work.\n\n4. **View of Central Park by Keith Haring:** Haring\u2019s urban and energetic motifs would complement Warhol's print, focusing on another famous NYC location.\n\n5. **Jazz Musicians by Jean-Michel Basquiat:** Basquiat\u2019s edgy, vibrant style depicting New York City's cultural scene can provide a dynamic contrast while maintaining the city theme.\n\nUltimately, choosing a complementary art print depends on your personal taste and the mood you wish to convey. These suggestions can help create a cohesive and visually appealing arrangement celebrating the charm and energy of New York City.",
